1
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:04,160
Previously on Babylon Berlin:

2
00:00:04,240 --> 00:00:07,120
I will guide you to the truth.

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:08,600
Gereon!

4
00:00:08,680 --> 00:00:10,800
-Did you go to war?
-I followed my brother.

5
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:13,440
I came back alone.
My mother never got over that.

6
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:15,800
For her, the wrong son came home.

7
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:18,880
Anno was officially declared dead.

8
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:21,520
-And now?
-We're here if you want us to.

9
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:23,680
Lotte? Where have you been?

10
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:24,880
Everywhere.

11
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:27,200
-I want to join homicide.
-No women there.

12
00:00:27,640 --> 00:00:30,440
-I don't do detective sergeants.
-Don't worry.

13
00:00:30,520 --> 00:00:32,280
Let's settle the matter between ourselves.

14
00:00:33,520 --> 00:00:35,040
What's the matter with you?

15
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:37,840
Get lost!
I don't want to see you again.

16
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:44,080
-Mr. Benda is not a murderer.
-He's the boss of the polit police.

17
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:46,920
No! Fritz!

18
00:00:47,080 --> 00:00:49,160
That Benda of yours, it was his people.

19
00:00:49,240 --> 00:00:51,720
Tell me what to do and I'll do it.

20
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:54,160
Fritz, what are you doing here?

21
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:55,320
You're mistaking me.

22
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:57,080
What's this, Daddy?

23
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:01,520
Do you recognise me?

24
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:03,720
Anno?

25
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:44,400
Stop! What are you doing?

26
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:46,520
You can't go out there.

27
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:49,120
Don't go out there! Stay inside, mate!

28
00:03:57,720 --> 00:04:00,320
We want our money back!

29
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:04,200
FIVE WEEKS EARLIER
20 SEPTEMBER 1929

30
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:12,280
-Why so many rolls?
-I don't know.

31
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:13,760
-Morning.
-Didn't he...

32
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:15,920
-Morning. When did you get home?
-Morning.

33
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:18,840
Late. Didn't want to disturb you.

34
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,080
Don't get upset.

35
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:33,880
WOMEN'S PENAL INSTITUTION
BERLIN-FRIEDRICHSHAIN

36
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:48,120
REJECTED
REJECTED

37
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:53,360
You are very persistent in this matter.

38
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:56,200
It's my heartfelt wish, Madam.

39
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:58,320
Greta Overbeck and I are close.

40
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:00,840
She doesn't give us that impression.

41
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:04,920
-Why ever not?
-It doesn't say that here.

42
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,280
She expressedly refuses to see anybody.

43
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:10,680
In particular DS Charlotte Ritter.

44
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:14,800
I'm just an assistant detective.

45
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:16,440
It says DS here.

46
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:19,920
Well, I can't help you there.

47
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,960
You're not even related.

48
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:24,520
Please sign here.

49
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:44,480
One more thing, Weintraub.
This is Mr Ulrich from police records.

50
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,080
What does the joker want?

51
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,800
Dactyloscopy.

52
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:50,520
-Fingerprints.
-Just a formality.

53
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:53,920
-For the discharge?
-For our files. Prophylactical.

54
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,400
Precautionary.

55
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,480
Please.

56
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:11,480
Well then, show me how you do it.

57
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,120
Thumb.

58
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:22,840
This is part of it.

59
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,760
GATE 2

60
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:51,520
Look at that, Stick-it-in Fuchs.

61
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,760
Welcome.

62
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:55,560
Well, well, well.

63
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,960
Clothes become people, huh?

64
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,560
Senor Walter.

65
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:03,560
Cigarette?

66
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:05,840
Here you are.

67
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:13,800
Vera?

68
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,320
Mr. Weintraub.

69
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,800
Caught red-handed.

70
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:44,960
You know what? You go ahead.

71
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:48,440
-I'll go for a little spin with madam.
-They're all waiting.

72
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:49,720
All the more suspense.

73
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,280
Come closer.

74
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:04,920
Don't you worry.

75
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:07,280
I won't hurt you. Come on.

76
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:29,680
FILM STUDIOS NEUBABELSBERG
POTSDAM-NOWAWES

77
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:33,000
We'll repeat the stage part
of "We've long lost each other",

78
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:35,640
the third and fourth shot.
Let's get to work.

79
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:37,400
-Quiet, please.
-We're rolling.

80
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:39,400
-Sound.
-Sound is running.

81
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:42,720
-Roll it.
-89-15, take two.

82
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,760
And action.

83
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:12,320
I don't see where you are going

84
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:17,120
When there is silence, and loneliness

85
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:23,000
Is heavy on my mind, and there is

86
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:27,920
A wind of grief and sorrow blowing

87
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:32,840
You don't want to tell me where

88
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:38,520
Your travels lead your contrary self

89
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:43,800
Then I must painfully but with purpose

90
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:47,800
Ask the question you are posing

91
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:54,240
It was looming inside of me
for a long time

92
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:58,760
It was pressing inside of me
for a long time

93
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:05,040
The longing that I once had

94
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:09,600
Indignation has displaced it now

95
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:16,920
We have long lost each other

96
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:22,480
We've grown apart in our hearts

97
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:27,880
We are the tail of yesterday's magic

98
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:33,400
And in our souls pain alone is burning

99
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:36,040
Yesterday is melting

100
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:38,760
Tomorrow is stony

101
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:43,640
Hope is making way to doom

102
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:49,160
There's no world where we are still safe

103
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:54,600
And lonely I go who knows where

104
00:13:56,760 --> 00:14:01,160
So much happiness was allotted to us

105
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:05,120
But now it's extinct in our souls

106
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:11,560
The long wait is followed by giving way

107
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:16,120
It's cold in my heart
I make no secret of it

108
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:23,440
We have long lost each other

109
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:28,760
We've grown apart in our hearts

110
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:34,880
We are the tail of yesterday's magic

111
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:40,120
And in our souls pain alone is burning

112
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:52,880
Betty?

113
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,400
Oh God.

114
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:17,560
What are you doing?

115
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:20,560
I'm sorry, my little flower.

116
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:24,000
First,
you have to do what you have to do.

117
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:26,160
And then...

118
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:29,400
...you can do what you want to do.

119
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:52,680
-Yes?
-This is Bellman.

120
00:15:52,760 --> 00:15:55,360
There's been an accident at the studio.

121
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:58,560
-What kind of accident?
-I, I, I...

122
00:15:58,920 --> 00:16:01,120
Stop the stammering, Bellman, talk.

123
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,760
Betty Winter is dead.

124
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:05,680
I'm coming.

125
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:43,880
-Oh, I'm sorry.
-I'm sorry.

126
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,600
Hello.

127
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:48,160
Hi.

128
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:52,320
You'll have to hurry if you want
to read all these before your exam.

129
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:54,840
No, I'm just returning them
to the library.

130
00:16:55,240 --> 00:16:56,320
May I?

131
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:01,200
-What's the exam?
-Forensics.

132
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:03,440
With Ulrich from the records department
and Gennat.

133
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:07,320
30 minutes with practical part, crime
scene analysis and securing of evidence.

134
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:09,240
Not exactly my strengths, I fear.

135
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:11,040
You can do this.

136
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:14,600
-You think?
-Why yes, of course.

137
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:22,200
Did you go to prison this morning?

138
00:17:23,520 --> 00:17:25,640
Yup. Greta doesn't want to see me.

139
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:27,720
She expressedly put that on record.

140
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:31,560
-The judgement is still out.
-I have to go.

141
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:34,160
Break a leg!

142
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:36,280
I didn't mean it like that.

143
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:39,680
Hi, boss.

144
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:43,400
-What's up?
-Stay there, we have to go downstairs.

145
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:46,160
-Where to?
-Babelsberg film studios.

146
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:48,520
Buddha's order,
we're to go there immediately.

147
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:52,440
Betty Winter.

148
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:55,520
One of the greatest, what am I saying,
the greatest hope

149
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:57,120
we have on stage and in film.

150
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,360
-Had.
-Pardon?

151
00:17:58,440 --> 00:17:59,960
Well, now she's...

152
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:02,160
This is a huge tragedy.

153
00:18:03,360 --> 00:18:05,120
And I only just met her.

154
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:07,960
-You mean personally?
-Less than a fortnight ago.

155
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:10,560
An autograph session in Babelsberg,

156
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:13,040
on Betty's birthday.

157
00:18:15,080 --> 00:18:17,560
Studio shoot for her last film.

158
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,720
Demon of Passion.

159
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:23,040
-Doesn't that already exist?
-Only on stage.

160
00:18:23,120 --> 00:18:26,120
But now a brandnew musical film,
with sound.

161
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,440
So you hear them talk, at the cinema?

162
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:30,200
Yes, and not just talk. They also sing.

163
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:31,960
Incredible woman.

164
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:34,800
No wonder the Americans
wanted to lure her there.

165
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:36,600
Who was that again?

166
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:38,200
Her husband, Tristan Rot.

167
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:40,120
He plays the male lead in the film.

168
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:42,440
Her husband? I thought he was queer.

169
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:45,240
Yes, he is, but he loved her.

170
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,200
Very much.

171
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:54,920
What's going on here?

172
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:57,240
Once again, the press was faster than us.

173
00:18:57,320 --> 00:18:59,320
Detective, what's going on here?

174
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,520
Do you know more
about the Betty Winter case?

175
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:03,680
CID, make way.

176
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:06,920
-No recordings.
-Article 118 of the Reich law:

177
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:09,960
-Every citizen has the right...
-But not now and not here.

178
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:12,320
-There is no censorship.
-That's enough.

179
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:14,960
Reinhold,
can't you do something? Please.

180
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:16,120
Close the gates.

181
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:22,680
Don't touch anything.

182
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:35,400
-Homicide division, hello.
-Homicide?

183
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:37,880
But it was an accident.

184
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:41,960
-Who are you?
-Jo Bellman, I'm the producer.

185
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:44,960
It was obviously an accident.

186
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:47,440
I mean, we all saw it...

187
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:49,040
We're here to clarify this.

188
00:19:49,120 --> 00:19:52,560
You stay with me.
Everyone else please wait off the set.

189
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:12,040
So, what exactly happened?

190
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:15,640
Case study no. 16. A lifeless body,

191
00:20:15,720 --> 00:20:19,160
found in the early morning
by the family gardener

192
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:22,800
in the property's garage,
identified by the wife,

193
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:24,880
who called the police immediately.

194
00:20:25,360 --> 00:20:28,160
All external circumstances
point towards suicide.

195
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:33,400
Miss...

196
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:37,720
-Ritter. Charlotte Ritter.
-Please, Miss Ritter. Ladies first.

197
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:42,800
What?

198
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:46,520
Explain the five steps of the procedure
to determine death,

199
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:47,920
Gennat method.

200
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:52,960
One, I get a first general overview
of the crime scene.

201
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:58,280
-Here?
-Exactly here.

202
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:00,000
Please don't touch.

203
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:15,080
Two, staff will look for evidence
and clues.

204
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:17,440
-How could this have happened?
-The lamp toppled

205
00:21:17,520 --> 00:21:19,280
and the screw heads were torn out.

206
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:21,240
Where's the cable for the spotlight?

207
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:24,080
-It's here.
-Don't touch!

208
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:26,720
It's quite the weight, 10kW.

209
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,520
Boss, shall we start?

210
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:32,200
-Search the set for clues. Gennat method.
-Yes, sir.

211
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:33,800
Gloves!

212
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,320
Very good, the gloves.

213
00:21:48,560 --> 00:21:50,640
Each detail is tagged.

214
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:01,840
The spotlight
was fixed with these screws.

215
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:03,240
Completely intact.

216
00:22:03,320 --> 00:22:05,600
Three, take pictures of the crime scene.

217
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:12,280
Four, witnesses are questioned.

218
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:14,440
My husband was with me all night.

219
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:18,000
One moment, Mrs Klopsch.
First the question, then the answer.

220
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,280
-Sorry.
-What's your name?

221
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:22,000
Tilly Brooks.

222
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:23,680
I see. Where are you from?

223
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:26,480
-Boston.
-Boston?

224
00:22:26,560 --> 00:22:28,200
Can you tell me in more detail?

225
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:30,800
I didn't see anything,
I was looking the other way.

226
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:34,440
-What about the husband, Tristan Rot?
-Tristan?

227
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:37,880
I didn't see anything,
I was up on the rope.

228
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:41,200
-Rot wasn't here today.
-It was his day off, as far as I know.

229
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:43,120
Who's responsible for the lighting?

230
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,800
Peter Glaser, the gaffer.

231
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:45,880
Where is he?

232
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:50,040
He only oversaw the set up. Then they
changed shift and he left with the others.

233
00:22:50,120 --> 00:22:52,120
Do you have his data on file?

234
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:54,920
-Of course.
-Where do you suspect fingerprints?

235
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:58,640
-Up there, on the balustrade.
-Correct. Take your time.

236
00:22:58,720 --> 00:23:01,680
On the door handle,
on the steering wheel...

237
00:23:05,040 --> 00:23:06,040
Keep going.

238
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:14,120
-And on the hose on the exhaust pipe.
-Very good.

239
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:17,920
Detective, the incident was filmed
by this camera.

240
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,720
We need to have it developed
immediately.

241
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:21,680
I ventured to have that arranged.

242
00:23:21,760 --> 00:23:22,920
Here you are.

243
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:24,520
Peter Glaser's personal file.

244
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,760
Very well. That's it from us now.

245
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:27,880
Mr Bellman.

246
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:37,920
The fifth and last step,

247
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:42,400
evacuation of the body and evaluation
of the results at headquarters.

248
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:45,360
Very good, Miss Ritter. Thank you. Next.

249
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:46,520
Detective!

250
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:52,880
We need you to sign
that it was an accident. Here.

251
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,960
You'll get it
once we've evaluated everything.

252
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:57,840
And if it was an accident.

253
00:24:08,040 --> 00:24:10,600
In the lab,
the dactyloscopic examination showed

254
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:14,600
that the deceased's fingerprints
are not congruent with those

255
00:24:14,680 --> 00:24:17,120
found on the hose on the exhaust pipe.

256
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:20,040
A comparison with the wife's fingerprints,

257
00:24:20,120 --> 00:24:21,400
seen on the right here,

258
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:24,600
confirm the assumption
that this was no suicide,

259
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:27,720
this was an insidious murder
by the wife.

260
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:29,480
Thank you.

261
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:31,680
And the motive?

262
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:36,160
-Revenge.
-Really?

263
00:24:36,240 --> 00:24:39,280
