374
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:40,160
-Because of the minutes?
-Minutiae.

375
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:43,360
-Can't you take the exam again?
-In a year.

376
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:45,760
What do I do without
investigatory powers for one year?

377
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:48,120
Now I'm not allowed
first access at crime scenes.

378
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:52,880
And Doris told me all male candidates
passed and they were a lot worse.

379
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:56,040
-So you need to be better.
-I am better!

380
00:32:58,960 --> 00:33:01,240
They simply don't want any women
in the department.

381
00:33:01,320 --> 00:33:02,320
I do.

382
00:33:07,280 --> 00:33:08,480
Charlotte, stop it.

383
00:33:09,600 --> 00:33:11,600
You're still an assistant detective.

384
00:33:11,680 --> 00:33:13,200
Even without the crime scene permit.

385
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:16,120
And I need your alert mind now.

386
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:18,640
Are you coming?

387
00:33:19,760 --> 00:33:20,760
Where to?

388
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:23,800
We're going to the pictures.

389
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:29,160
You have to learn to distinguish between
relevant and irrelevant questions.

390
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:31,440
Is it irrelevant
if you know what minutiae are?

391
00:33:32,080 --> 00:33:35,560
The young woman established
the circumstances of the crime perfectly.

392
00:33:35,640 --> 00:33:37,600
And then you threw her off track.

393
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:39,840
I asked for simple technical knowledge.

394
00:33:39,920 --> 00:33:42,120
It's your credo, Criminal Counsellor.

395
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:45,800
The biggest secrets are hidden
in the smallest of details.

396
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:49,240
Precision is important in our work.

397
00:33:50,200 --> 00:33:52,600
But pettiness is harmful.

398
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:55,760
This is where we disagree, Mr Ulrich.

399
00:33:58,800 --> 00:33:59,800
Mr Gräf.

400
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:02,480
Go ahead.

401
00:34:42,560 --> 00:34:43,720
Appalling.

