484
00:41:06,960 --> 00:41:09,960
Right, now we'll put everything
in his bed linen.

485
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:18,720
Through all of history

486
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:21,440
A breeze of emancipation is blowing

487
00:41:21,720 --> 00:41:24,720
From human beings to infusoria

488
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:28,040
Woman wants to be on the throne
everywhere

489
00:41:28,480 --> 00:41:32,560
From the Amazons to the girls of Berlin...

490
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:35,400
Look at this. Disgusting thing.

491
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:36,720
Throw it away!

492
00:41:37,320 --> 00:41:38,760
What men can do

493
00:41:38,840 --> 00:41:40,800
We've been doing for a long time

494
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:44,080
And maybe a whole lot more

495
00:41:45,440 --> 00:41:48,640
Out with the men in the Reichstag

496
00:41:48,720 --> 00:41:51,800
And out with the men in the Landtag

497
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:55,440
And out with the men in the manor house

498
00:41:55,520 --> 00:41:58,960
We'll turn it into a woman's house

499
00:41:59,040 --> 00:42:01,960
Out with the men in existence

500
00:42:02,040 --> 00:42:04,600
And out with the men who are still here

501
00:42:04,680 --> 00:42:07,520
And out with the men who are over there

502
00:42:07,600 --> 00:42:10,240
They should already have gone

503
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:13,680
Yeah, out with the men in the den

504
00:42:13,760 --> 00:42:16,880
And into those places with the women

505
00:42:19,600 --> 00:42:20,840
Well, there you go.

506
00:43:45,080 --> 00:43:47,920
Truth is a treacherous beast.

507
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:52,920
Our alliance with the past is diffused
by our desire to form versions

508
00:43:53,000 --> 00:43:56,680
and variations of our experiences.

509
00:43:57,120 --> 00:44:01,000
But there are no versions of the truth.

510
00:44:02,160 --> 00:44:04,160
The truth is singular.

511
00:44:05,760 --> 00:44:10,080
There is a subject across from me today,
let's call him Siegfried.

512
00:44:11,360 --> 00:44:13,360
The challenge is to demonstrate with him

513
00:44:13,720 --> 00:44:18,880
how much man tends to get tangled up
in lies and self-deception,

514
00:44:18,960 --> 00:44:22,560
solely because of his desire
to have everything he experiences

515
00:44:22,640 --> 00:44:25,920
and which seems incomprehensible
make sense.

516
00:44:26,440 --> 00:44:28,640
Siegfried, are you ready?

517
00:44:29,320 --> 00:44:30,320
Yes.

518
00:44:30,480 --> 00:44:34,200
Focus. Don't waste any time
for your answers.

519
00:44:34,280 --> 00:44:38,120
The more time an answer has
to follow a question,

520
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:41,280
the less room there is for the truth.

521
00:44:42,520 --> 00:44:46,280
So answer my questions
immediately now.

522
00:44:46,360 --> 00:44:47,360
Yes.

523
00:44:48,000 --> 00:44:50,000
-Do you love the ocean?
-Yes.

524
00:44:50,080 --> 00:44:51,840
-Do you love mountains?
-No.

525
00:44:52,160 --> 00:44:53,880
-Do you love cigarettes?
-Yes.

526
00:44:53,960 --> 00:44:56,560
-Have you ever killed a human being?
-Yes.

527
00:44:57,120 --> 00:44:59,400
-When did you kill them?
-In the war.

